Yes. The order should be:

1. Add the comment/code.
2. Run a quick syntax check.
3. Build the new image.
4. Run the new image.
5. Run the curl capture commands.
6. Diff against the Phase 2 baseline.

Use this flow:

python3 -m py_compile scripts/generate-pxe-content.py

Then rebuild/push or build locally the new pxe-content image.

On the PXE VM, stop the existing service/container first if you’re testing manually:

systemctl stop pxe-content.service
podman rm -f pxe-content 2>/dev/null || true

Run the new image:

podman run -d \
  --name pxe-content \
  --security-opt label=disable \
  -p 18080:8080 \
  -v /aerolit_rhel8_standard/extracted_isos:/iso:ro,Z \
  -e PXE_SERVER=192.168.98.148 \
  -e PXE_PORT=18080 \
  registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com/lit/containers/pxe-content:latest

Then capture Phase 3A output:

mkdir -p /tmp/pxe-phase3a
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/boot.ipxe \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase3a/boot.ipxe
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/generated/isos.txt \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase3a/isos.txt
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/generated/status.json \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase3a/status.json
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/ks/rhel8-minimal.ks \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase3a/rhel8-minimal.ks
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/ui/background.png
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/rhel8/images/pxeboot/vmlinuz
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/rhel8/images/pxeboot/initrd.img

Then compare:

diff -u /tmp/pxe-phase2-refactor/boot.ipxe /tmp/pxe-phase3a/boot.ipxe
diff -u /tmp/pxe-phase2-refactor/isos.txt /tmp/pxe-phase3a/isos.txt
diff -u /tmp/pxe-phase2-refactor/status.json /tmp/pxe-phase3a/status.json
diff -u /tmp/pxe-phase2-refactor/rhel8-minimal.ks /tmp/pxe-phase3a/rhel8-minimal.ks

For 3A, the ideal result is no diff. If boot.ipxe has a diff, show me before merging.